Keep a DHCP lease alive for a CARP virtual IP.

On a DHCP-assigned WAN the ISP only routes an address while it has an active DHCP
lease bound to a MAC, so a static CARP VIP receives no traffic. This plugin runs a
small daemon that keeps a DHCP lease alive for a chosen chaddr (normally the CARP
virtual MAC of an existing CARP VirtualIP), so the VIP address is routed and can
fail over between two OPNsense nodes.

An HA CARP setup needs several concurrent DHCP addresses on the line (one per node
plus the shared VIP). That is typically feasible on CGNAT links (abundant RFC 6598
shared space) but rare on public IPv4.

WWW: https://github.com/toreamun/opnsense-plugins
